page.title: 12Festival Report, Prickwillow
page.content: When I went to Prickwillow on Sunday 23 June 1985 I went to the{Pumping {Engine Museum.}The pumps pumps 140 {tons}of water a minute. The engine is so large that only half of it is in the museum. I went to see the vintage car display near the pumping museum. Later I went on the tractor ride past Mr Rice's Peat farm then we saw the rabbits. { The sack race at Prickwill Festival On Saturday I went in for the sack racs at Prickwillow Festival so did my brother, I came first and my brother came third the prize was a bag of jelly babies. Then we saw some people clay pidgeon shooting at the Higham{Club.}The next day we went to the vintage car display, one of them was a model T Ford.
